Certificate for Mock Poll amended
BHOPAL: Election Commission has amended draft of Mock Poll certificate. The commission has directed office of the Chief Electoral Officer to inform about it to election duty staff and ensure adherence to these directives during Lok Sabha elections. 
Now, serial numbers of ballot units and control units of EVMs used in polling booths should be written in the Mock Poll certificate apart from number of candidate-wise votes, number of votes visible during scrutiny of votes cast in Mock Poll and print paper slips. It should also be mentioned in the Mock Poll certificate whether number of votes seen on CU tally with the total number of votes cast for candidates. If more than one CU is used in a polling booth than the serial numbers of all ballot units should be written. The commission has directed to pass on the information to all election duty staff.
